In addition, the club reached the final of the 1999–2000 UEFA Cup (losing on <a3_0>penalties<a3_0/> to <b7_0><b8_0>Galatasaray<b8_0/><b7_0/>), were victorious in the 2003 and 2005 FA Cups, and won the <a4_0>Premier League<a4_0/> in 2003–04 without losing a single match, an achievement which earned the side the nickname "The Invincibles".
